Greek Unions Call 24-Hour Strike May 11 Against New Measures

-- B y   T o m   S t o u k a s
-- 
2011-04-18T14:06:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-18/greek-unions-call-24-hour-strike-may-11-against-new-measures.html
Greece ’s General Confederation of
Labor will hold a 24-hour strike on May 11 against new austerity
measures, Georgia Totsi, a spokeswoman for the country’s largest
private-sector union, said in a phone interview today.  ADEDY, the country’s biggest public sector union, will also
take part in the strike, ADEDY spokeswoman Despina Spanou said
over the phone.  To contact the reporter on this story:
